github: https://github.com/yawn-ai/.yawn
license: MIT
copyright_holder: The Yawn Company

canonical_root: readme.yawn
compatibility_readme: readme.md

summary: >
  .yawn is a tiny open filesystem for shared mental models, lived agency,
  material records, access history, and next-move rationale.

canonical_sentence: >
  .yawn is the simplest possible interface for structured movement.

root_loop:
  - see the frame
  - name the lacuna
  - choose a bounded move
  - gather proof
  - replay what changed

file_priority:
  - human-readable first
  - machine-addressable second
  - proof-bound when promoted

