boundary:
  - signal is not instruction
  - resonance is not proof
  - coincidence is not command
  - memory is not objective record
  - ai output is not authority
  - intensity is not truth
  - only proof updates the map

first_move:
  instruction: >
    Copy templates/basic.yawn into a new file. Name one thing that has
    attention. Do not force the answer.
  proof: "You can point to one clearer next question."
  replay: "What changed after naming it?"

material_record_rule: >
  When an agent or human uses an important file, tool, account, external
  service, backup, GitHub surface, or other access path, record what was used,
  why it mattered, what changed, and what proof or risk remains.

